import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
from pygam import LinearGAM
from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import pairwise_kernels
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
from sklearn.base import BaseEstimator, RegressorMixin

def generate_data(n_samples=1000, noise_std=0.5):
    np.random.seed(42)
    X = np.random.uniform(0, 20, n_samples)
    y = np.cos(X**2 / 12)
    noise = np.random.normal(0, noise_std, n_samples)
    y_noisy = y + noise
    return X, y_noisy

class NadarayaWatsonRegressor(BaseEstimator, RegressorMixin):
    def __init__(self, kernel="rbf", gamma=None):
        self.kernel = kernel
        self.gamma = gamma

    def fit(self, X, y):
        self.X_ = X
        self.y_ = y
        return self

    def predict(self, X):
        K_x = pairwise_kernels(X, self.X_, metric=self.kernel, gamma=self.gamma)
        epsilon = 1e-8 # Prevent the denomenator from being zero or nan
        weights = K_x / (np.sum(K_x, axis=1)[:, np.newaxis] + epsilon)
        return np.dot(weights, self.y_)

X, y_noisy = generate_data()
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y_noisy, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

gam = LinearGAM().fit(X_train, y_train)

params = {"gamma": np.logspace(-3, 3, 10)}
nw_regressor = GridSearchCV(NadarayaWatsonRegressor(), params, cv=5)
nw_regressor.fit(X_train[:, np.newaxis], y_train)

gam_mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, gam.predict(X_test))
nw_mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, nw_regressor.predict(X_test[:, np.newaxis]))

print(f"GAM MSE: {gam_mse:.4f}")
print(f"Nadaraya-Watson MSE: {nw_mse:.4f}")

X_plot = np.linspace(0, 20, 1000)
y_true = np.cos(X_plot**2 / 12)
gam_pred = gam.predict(X_plot)
nw_pred = nw_regressor.predict(X_plot[:, np.newaxis])

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(X_plot, y_true, label="Ground truth", color="black", linestyle="--")
plt.scatter(X_train, y_train, color="blue", alpha=0.2, label="Train data")
plt.plot(X_plot, gam_pred, label="GAM", color="red")
plt.plot(X_plot, nw_pred, label="Nadaraya-Watson", color="green")
plt.xlabel("X")
plt.ylabel("y")
plt.legend()
plt.title("Comparison of GAM and Nadaraya-Watson Regressor")
plt.show()

GAM MSE: 0.3432
Nadaraya-Watson MSE: 0.2353

from sklearn.model_selection import KFold, train_test_split, GridSearchCV
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
import numpy as np

def perform_10_fold_cv(X, y):
    kfold = KFold(n_splits=10, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    gam_rmse_list = []
    nw_rmse_list = []

    lam = np.logspace(-3, 3, 10)
    gamma = np.logspace(-3, 3, 10)

    scaler = StandardScaler()

    for train_index, test_index in kfold.split(X):
        X_train, X_test = X[train_index], X[test_index]
        y_train, y_test = y[train_index], y[test_index]

        # Standardize the features
        X_train = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
        X_test = scaler.transform(X_test)

        # GAM model
        gam = LinearGAM().gridsearch(X_train, y_train, lam=lam)
        gam_pred = gam.predict(X_test)
        gam_rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, gam_pred))
        gam_rmse_list.append(gam_rmse)

        # Nadaraya-Watson model
        nw_params = {"gamma": gamma}
        nw_cv = GridSearchCV(NadarayaWatsonRegressor(kernel="rbf"), nw_params, cv=5)
        nw_cv.fit(X_train, y_train)
        nw_pred = nw_cv.predict(X_test)
        nw_rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, nw_pred))
        nw_rmse_list.append(nw_rmse)

    return gam_rmse_list, nw_rmse_list


gam_rmse_list, nw_rmse_list = perform_10_fold_cv(X, y)

print(f"GAM RMSE (mean  std): {np.mean(gam_rmse_list):.4f}  {np.std(gam_rmse_list):.4f}")
print(f"Nadaraya-Watson RMSE (mean  std): {np.mean(nw_rmse_list):.4f}  {np.std(nw_rmse_list):.4f}")
